<title>Maltreatment In Care</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<p><b><a NAME="maltreatmentInCare">Maltreatment In Care</a></b><br>
<br>
A substantiated investigative finding which meets the definition/criteria of child abuse, 
neglect, sexual abuse or emotional abuse that is attributable to a foster parent, 
relative or non-relative caregiver or employee of a public or private child caring agency, 
institution or private residential treatment facility and the victim is a child in the 
temporary or permanent custody of this state or another state
<br/>
<br>
<p><b><a NAME="policyViolation">Policy Violation</a></b><br>
<br>
Violations of foster care policies are actions by a foster parent that breach any foster home 
approval policy or procedure but do not constitute abuse or neglect.
<br>
<br>

